**ACCOUNT SUSPENSION**

Sent follows ups if the customers do not pay and if they fail to make payment in 7 days of due date, you can suspend the account from Admin CP on 10th day. Use the option ( SUSPEND FOR NON PAYMENT). Then send following reply template:

```
Hello,
We are sorry to inform you that your account has been suspended due to non-payment.
If you are having any problems with payment, please let us know. We may be able to work an arrangement with you. 
We'd like to keep you as a customer and of course, help your business grow. 
If you do not wish to keep this server, please let us know instead of letting it expire. 
We'd appreciate any feedback that you can provide us.
We hope to hear from you soon.
```

**ACCOUNT CANCELLATION**

If CX reply that they want to cancel, ask for reason and if it is due to our service issue like performance, application failure etc, inform Peter by sending an email. If cx simply want to close the account, go ahead and submit cancellation from Admin portal ( First Delete VMs > after 72 hours do CANCELLATION)

If no reply from customer after suspending the account, wait for another 14 days (for new customers) and atleast 20 days (for old customers) and then, delete VM from Admin CP and sent following reply and close ticket. (For old customers: we can give some more time to pay invoice, so no need to cancel it very fast)

```
Hello,
Since we didn't receive any replies from your end, we are sorry to inform that your account will be cancelled without any further notice.
Thank you.
```

Complete deletion will occur  after 72 hours, so you have to make sure that VMs are totally deleted from account and then do account cancellation (Cancel by Request or Cancel - due to non payment).

**IMP : You have to check the file on daily basis and SUSPEND/VM DELETION/CANCELLATION must be done on WEEK DAYS ONLY. Always double check if CX made payment or not before proceeding with any action. If paid, clear the entry from file and close the respective ticket**. 


**Do not forget to add the date on which you suspend an account/delete a VM**.
